[REQUIREMENT]
UID: FR-001
TITLE: Binary Sidecar Format Support
STATEMENT: The system shall support binary sidecar file formats (.bin and .rkyv) in addition to JSON format, providing superior performance and storage efficiency.
RATIONALE: Binary formats provide 50-70% size reduction and 3-10x faster read/write performance compared to JSON, addressing performance bottlenecks in large photo collections.
PRIORITY: Critical
STATUS: Pending

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: FR-001.1
TITLE: Multi-Format Sidecar Storage
STATEMENT: The SidecarManager shall support storing sidecar data in JSON (.json), Binary (.bin), and Rkyv (.rkyv) formats with automatic format detection and fallback.
RATIONALE: Multi-format support enables gradual migration from JSON to binary formats while maintaining backward compatibility.
PRIORITY: Critical
STATUS: Pending

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: FR-001.2
TITLE: Format Abstraction Layer
STATEMENT: All detector modules shall use the SidecarManager abstraction layer for sidecar operations, eliminating hardcoded JSON serialization calls.
RATIONALE: Abstraction layer ensures consistent sidecar handling regardless of format and enables seamless format migration.
PRIORITY: Critical
STATUS: Pending

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: FR-001.3
TITLE: Rust Integration for Binary Formats
STATEMENT: The SidecarManager shall delegate binary format operations to the Rust sidecar utility when available, falling back to Python implementations when Rust is unavailable.
RATIONALE: Rust integration provides high-performance binary serialization while maintaining compatibility for systems without Rust tooling.
PRIORITY: Critical
STATUS: Pending

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: FR-001.4
TITLE: Automatic Format Detection
STATEMENT: The system shall automatically detect sidecar file format by attempting multiple file extensions (.bin, .rkyv, .json) and content-based format detection.
RATIONALE: Automatic format detection enables seamless reading of sidecars regardless of format and eliminates manual format specification.
PRIORITY: High
STATUS: Pending

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: FR-001.5
TITLE: Format Preference Configuration
STATEMENT: The system shall use binary format (.bin) as the default format for new sidecar files, with JSON format as fallback when binary support is unavailable.
RATIONALE: Binary format preference optimizes performance and storage while maintaining JSON fallback for compatibility.
PRIORITY: High
STATUS: Pending

